Review: While attending this studio, I enjoyed my time with the instructors and like the classes. Unfortunately, when it came time to cancel, it was not so simple. I was given multiple misrepresentations by various staff members, and relied upon such misrepresentations to my detriment. When I finally got in touch with Vanessa, after leaving multiple messages over the course of 9 days,( the only person who seemingly has any authority in the studio), I was dismayed at her response to my inquiries and concerns. I was unfairly charged for a month of classes when I made very clear to the studio months prior that I had moved and no longer intended to be a member of that home studio. When I asked to cancel, I was told that it was taken care of and I was not sent a cancellation form. Apparently I should have known the procedures and protocols for cancellation better than OTF's own staff members. Due to the studio's own fault, I was charged a full month and after Vanessa FINALLY returned a phone call, I was given no choice but to use or lose my classes with less than half the month to go. To add insult to injury, she told me that I was "lucky" not to be charged an additional month, although such charge would have been wholly unwarranted. When the "notes" on my account were read back to me, I was very surprised at how inaccurate they were. For example, I had called to fix a minor issue with payment for a class in another studio (a studio I am happy with and will likely attend in the future), but the notes reflect that I was somehow "complaining." I do not trust the notes that the staff members rely upon to the detriment of their own customers. I will not be returning nor would I recommend anyone to attend this studio when there are several others (I love Astoria, Bayside and Mamaroneck to name a few), that are more professional, courteous and give you just as great of a workout.

Apparently I should have known the procedures and protocols for cancellation better than OTF's own staff members. Due to the studio's own fault, I was charged a full month and after Vanessa FINALLY returned a phone call, I was given no choice but to use or lose my classes with less than half the month to go. To add insult to injury, she told me that I was "lucky" not to be charged an additional month, although such charge would have been wholly unwarranted. When the "notes" on my account were read back to me, I was very surprised at how inaccurate they were. For example, I had called to fix a minor issue with payment for a class in another studio (a studio I am happy with and will likely attend in the future), but the notes reflect that I was somehow "complaining." I do not trust the notes that the staff members rely upon to the detriment of their own customers. I will not be returning nor would I recommend anyone to attend this studio when there are several others (I love Astoria, Bayside and Mamaroneck to name a few), that are more professional, courteous and give you just as great of a workout.

prompt:

Review: It truly pains me to leave a bad review, but after my experience trying to cancel this membership, I have no choice. I have been trying to cancel this membership since may, and we are now in august. I loved orange theory's classes and coaches, they will give you great service until you try to cancel. They make the process almost impossible and good luck getting a refund for the months they will charge you after you decide to cancel. There is always some issue with "corporate".
I went at the end of April, filled out a cancellation form which they claim not to have on file. I sent out a change of address form because since I moved I could not reasonably commute to forest hills. They said they were going to cancel the membership in June and could not refund may. They charged june, and charged july again.
I had to call back they said I was going to get a refund for both months. I got receipt for a refund for July, nothing for June. I am calling these people every week all I got was a receipt, no actual refund. I called my bank, they have nothing from OTF, yet they said everything was done on their end. So all I have is a fake return receipt for one month.
I call again and again trying to speak to the owner, Vanessa, but apparently she is never available.  When it comes to bringing new business (members) or getting a more expensive membership, I can assure you they will call you back and chase you around. However, when you try to leave they make it almost impossible and will keep on charging you for as long as they can.
This has been the most frustrating experience trying to cancel this membership, and it's sad because OTF's workouts are great and the coaches are amazing. However, it just feels scamish how they just keep on charging you and make it impossible to cancel.

Last but not least, I called the studio and brought this to the attention of the front desk over one week ago and I asked to have a manager call me to discuss.  I have yet to receive a phone call.

Review: It pains me to leave a negative review as I have been an Orange Theory member for the past two years. While most OTF locations are great, the customer service at the Forest Hills location is extremely poor. I've only been late twice, both times due to severe train delays, and showed up for class as soon as I could. Despite this, the representative informed me that I couldn't enter the class, which I understand as per policy. However, what is disappointing is that despite my effort to arrive and explain the situation, they still insisted on charging me for being late. This lack of understanding and flexibility, especially given the circumstances, is disheartening. In addition, they tried to charge me for a class that I attended. I hope the management at Forest Hills can improve their customer service and show a bit more empathy towards their loyal members.

prompt:
Classify the following review of a fitness studio into one or more of these categories: customer service, pricing, billing practises, overall experience, coaches, cleanliness, variety. Example Review: "The coach is excellent but the pricing too expensive.", Expected Output: "coaches,pricing". Review: This location makes it really hard to join their center. This was my second attempt to go. After my experience, I just joined another gym around the corner.
The first time was for a 5:30am class. I arrived at 5:15 since it was so early. The person who oriented wouldn't let me take the class since she said that there wasn't enough time to orient. Yet we spent the first 15 minutes going over merchandise, bathrooms. I am an athlete and familiar with HR zones. Instead I wish she was flexible and could orient me to the equipment and coach. She already knew I had a concept2 rower in my basement. Then I could start a few minutes late while she oriented me to the brand. Anyway she finished her orientation just before 5:30 and still wouldn't consider letting me try the class.  I was excited to be part of OTF since I‚Äôve heard good things. But I was so turned off. It was an early morning to wake up for nothing.
I waited 6 months before attempting to go again. This time I was THREE minutes late. I explained that I already went through the first half of the orientation, but the front staff was still not willing to make any adjustments.
It's unfortunate that the Forest Hills location is so unaccommodating given the local competition.  Most of my friends at other sites very much enjoy their OTF experience.

title: Orangetheory Fitness
review_text:
My terrible experience started before I stepped in the Forest Hills branch. I called them just to get information about joining and to compare with another OTF gym I had called a few mins prior, located near my workplace. I had been a loyal member of NYSC for 13 years until COVID. I had already taken the free OTF and was ready to join - credit card in hand when I called. I just wanted to know if there was a difference in the branches near work versus near home before paying.
The person on the phone was rude and unhelpful. She said I needed come to the gym for information. I told her I was able to obtain pricing info from a different branch just 5 mins ago and asked why she couldn‚Äôt give the same info about her branch. Her dry response: I can‚Äôt, you have to come in person.
So, they lost another customer. If you read all other 1 star reviews you‚Äôll come to the same conclusion I did. Do not join this branch. I‚Äôm not even sure I will join OTF at this point.
Corporate should take a hard look at this Forest Hills franchise.

Example Review: "The coach is excellent but the pricing too expensive.", Expected Output: "coaches,pricing". Review: OTF forest hills is astonishing!!!! The whole crew is the entire package, from the front, manager, and coach (Al, Alex, Kyle, Jacqueline) are marvelous!!!! Including a super cute greeter, Lola the Boston Terrier! Lola could be an emotional support dog!*
I appreciate all coaches correcting my form! My personal experience is I never be someone who is considered sporty. I lacked self-esteem for a boutique gym like this since I thought everyone in the boutique gym was viewed as a gym nut or a celebgram, but I was wrong. When I walked in for the first time nine months ago, Vanessa asked me what my fitness goal was; I didn't even know my fitness goal; I just simply said, "losing all fat I got from quarantine 2020". In the beginning, I focused on the form and the effectiveness more the weight of my neighbor to prevent the injury and get a better outcome! In my first week, it was a challenge to run one mile. TRUST me, and the first mile is the hardest! Kyle was pushing me to complete the challenge; I was the last person to finish on that day! Al always puts a lot of effort to work on my upper body (my weakness), and Alex constantly challenges me by placing a cone for a core workout (my favorite part)!! Review: Update: I first wrote this review several years ago but felt the need to update because of one instructor in particular.
Alex is, hands down, the best coach I‚Äôve ever seen at an Orangetheory - across the 10+ studios I‚Äôve been to in 5 states. Being in a class with him is like having a personal trainer, given his attention to detail and hands-on approach whether it is giving tips, fixing form, or even just dropping by to say you‚Äôre doing great. This dude can multitask like crazy, and even in a full class he somehow makes time to check up on everyone. You can tell he genuinely enjoys helping people, even staying after class to explain the correct forms in more detail. Sometimes his classes run over but it‚Äôs because he‚Äôs being too helpful (lol). After having been in a few of his classes now, I felt compelled to come here to commend him - I hope OTF Forest Hills keeps him for a long time because his presence alone elevates this studio.
My original review:
I travel a lot so I‚Äôve been to 4 Orangetheory studios across 3 different states, here is what is provided (and not provided) at this specific gym:
- No free borrowing of heart rate monitors (studios in small cities will lend them to you for free, not the case in NY)
- No towels (the only studio I‚Äôve ever been to that does not provide towels)
- No surcharge fee (most NYC studios have a special, additional fee for booking if it‚Äôs not your home studio; in Manhattan it‚Äôs $20 and in Brooklyn it‚Äôs $10)
- Filtered water (from tap, but has a filter so it‚Äôs not just a drinking fountain)
- Free lockers with built-in locks
- Showers
- Coat rack
- No pressure to sign up for a membership if you‚Äôre only on a class package (some studios can be very pushy)
The staff and trainers are friendly, they make a genuine effort to learn names and remember faces. Really the only thing they can improve upon is providing small towels. I don‚Äôt have a monthly membership so I can‚Äôt speak to any billing experiences but the lack of studio surcharge at this location is a big win for traveling package holders like me.
